{left}
{p} {p}
Well, that's all you need to know. As always, keep in mind that what
I've suggested here could be incorrect. If you are serious about
building this, *please* double check my PSU pinouts from another
source, and double check your own connections before you power
anything up! I don't accept any responsibility for any of the
information presented here; use it at your own risk. To the best of
my knowledge, and to the best of my ability, I've tried to make all
pinouts and information listed here as accurate as possible. I've put
the circuit through a software simulator, and nothing blew up... :)
{p} {p}
Next month I'll report how my own summing amp goes, ie. whether the
whole idea is flawed or not ;) If you make this yourself, tell us
about it!
{p} {p}
- Paul Harvey (paul@aio.co.uk)
